{{Dialogue|Khabarakh|<nowiki></nowiki>''Ilyr'ush mir lakh svoril'lae. Mir'lae karah siv Mal'ary'ush vir'ae Vader'ush.''<nowiki></nowiki>|Leia Organa Solo|Can you understand it?|C-3PO|To a degree. It appears to be a dialect of the ancient trade language&mdash;|attr=Leia Organa Solo asks C-3PO if he understood [[Khabarakh]] speaking Honoghran|src=<ref name="Dark Force Rising">''[[Dark Force Rising]]''</ref>}}
'''Honoghran''', or '''Noghrese''' was the native [[Language/Legends|language]] of the [[Noghri/Legends|Noghri]] [[Species/Legends|species]] from [[Honoghr/Legends|Honoghr]].<ref name="u">''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]''</ref> Upon first encountering Noghri speaking Honoghran, the [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] only partially understood the language and believed it was a dialect of an ancient [[Trade language/Legends|trade language]].<ref name="Dark Force Rising" />

Most Noghri were fluent in both Honoghran and [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]], although with whispered, chilling and soft voices. However, they were usually only literate in their own language.<ref name="u" />

Aliens who regularly dealt with Noghri, including as Grand Admiral [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]<ref name="res">''[[Rebellion Era Sourcebook]]''</ref> and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]],<ref name="cr">''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook]]''</ref><ref name="rcr">''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Revised Core Rulebook]]''</ref> sometimes learned Honoghran to speak with them.

==Glossary of terms==
*''[[Dukha]]'': Communal building
*''[[Dynast]]'': Clan leader
*''[[Maitrakh]]'': Clan leader
*''[[Mal'ary'ush]]'': Daughter of the savior
*''[[Pirkha]]'': Area of land
*''Sha'vah'': Quiet<ref name="DFR p126">''[[Dark Force Rising]]'' p126</ref><ref name="DFR2">[[Dark Force Rising 2|''Dark Force Rising'' 2]]</ref>

